HEADWORD: Rhusma
<hw>Rhus"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Rusma</er>.]</ety> <def>A mixtire of caustic lime and orpiment, or
tersulphide of arsenic, -- used in the depilation of hides.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

